definition.value: A physical descriptor for the lower explosive limit in air as a percentage by volume at room temperature
A physical descriptor for the minimum explosive concentration.
A physical descriptor of the ratio of the density of chemical substance to the density of a reference substance. The reference substance is usually water for liquids or air for gases.
A descriptor of the relative density of gases referenced to air as 1, which indicates how many times a gas is heavier than air at the same temperature.
A descriptor of the density of a vapour in relation in that of hydrogen, defined as the mass of a certain volume of the given substance divided by the mass of the same volume of hydrogen.
A physical descriptor for the lowest concentration of an odorant chemical entity that is perceivable by the human sense of smell.
A physical descriptor which gives a measure of the acidity or basicity of an aqueous solution, defined as the decimal logarithm of the reciprocal of the hydrogen ion activity in a solution.
A physical descriptor of the rate of evaporation of a liquid under standard conditions.
A physical descriptor of the lowest temperature at a substance will spontaneously ignite in a normal atmosphere without an external source of ignition.
A physical descriptor for the time it takes for half of a portion of substance of a given type to decompose in soil under standard conditions.
Identifier used by the Chemical Abstracts Service database.
A seven-digit identifier for chemical substances for regulatory purposes within the European Union.
A descriptor that specifies the integer count of metal atoms in a given chemical entity.
A descriptor that specifies the integer count of oxygen atoms in a given chemical entity.
An identifying descriptor which is used within a particular database system to identify a chemical system.
A preferred name in ChemSpider by virtue of having been validated by a curator.
A molecular entity name in the ChemSpider database which has not been validated by a curator.
A chemical database identifier which has been validated by a curator.
A role inhering in a person which is realized when they perform a curation task.
A planned process in which a person bearing a curator role confirms an association between a CRID and an information content entity.
A planned process in which a person bearing a curator role marks an association between a chemical name and an information content entity as unconfirmed.
A planned process in which a person bearing a curator role modifies a CRID registry.
A planned process in which a person bearing a curator role confirms an association between a chemical name and an information content entity.
A planned process in which a person bearing a curator role deprecates an association between a chemical name and an information content entity.
A planned process in which an association between a CRID and an information content entity is deprecated.
This can be done automatically; it does not need a person bearing a curator role.
A planned process in which an association between a CRID and an information content entity is marked as unconfirmed.
A ChemSpider validated synonym that has been identified as a title by the ChemSpider software.

label.value: average molecular weight descriptor calculated by ACD/Labs PhysChem software library version 12.01
monoisotopic molecular weight descriptor calculated by ACD/Labs PhysChem software library version 12.01

definition.value: A descriptor that describes the energy range in a solid where no electron states can exist. In graphs of the electron band structure of solids, the band gap generally refers to the energy difference (in electron volts) between the top of the valence band and the bottom of the conduction band in insulators and semiconductors. [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Band_gap]
A descriptor describing the mass of the metal element component of a composite substance.

label.value: molecular formula calculated by ACD/Labs PhysChem software library version 12.01

definition.value: Molecular formula for a chemical structure as calculated by ACD/Labs PhysChem software library version 12.01.
The ratio of a dissolved substance in a two-phase system, giving a measure of the difference in solubility of the substance in the two phases.
A parameter data item is a data item that plays the role of a parameter to a software method.
A numeric data item is a data item which has a value which is numeric.
A textual data item is a data item which has a value that has at least some non-numeric characters included in it.
A software message data item is a data item that plays the role of a message generated by a software implementation, for example, an error, warning or success message.
A numeric data format specification is a data format specification for data items which are numeric, that is, they contain only numeric values.
A textual data format specification is a specification of the format of data items which are textual, that is, they consist of character data.
A property of solids which is the total surface area of a material per unit of mass, solid or bulk volume, or cross-sectional area.
Descriptor that returns the group in the periodic table of a given atom.
An InChI-like descriptor for nanomaterials.
